title: Cafe-Obrador Okapi
typeOfFood: Vegan-friendly, Lacto, Ovo, Mediterranean, Take-out, Catering, Spanish, Non-veg
description: Serves meat, veg options available. Its small menu offers vegan-friendly food including hummus, guacamole, tapenade, couscous, and falafel. Has soymilk for drinks. Note that the tzatziki and queso frito are mistakenly marked vegan but are not. Owner aims to use locally-sourced and seasonal ingredients to minimize carbon footprint.
